text.section:
The Chief Boiler Inspector or a deputy boiler inspector shall have free access, during reasonable hours, to any premises in the State:
to determine whether a boiler or pressure vessel is being constructed for use or installed in the State in accordance with this subtitle;
to inspect or investigate an accident or explosion that involves a boiler or pressure vessel;
to make an inspection required under this subtitle; or
to investigate an inspection of a special inspector.
